note.p:
Pub. L. 104–134, title III, § 31001(bb), Apr. 26, 1996, 110 Stat. 1321–380, provided that: “The Director of the Office of Management and Budget shall— “(1) review the standards and policies of each Federal agency for compromising, writing-down, forgiving, or discharging indebtedness arising from programs of the agency;
“(2) determine whether those standards and policies are consistent and protect the interests of the United States;
“(3) in the case of any Federal agency standard or policy that the Director determines is not consistent or does not protect the interests of the United States, direct the head of the agency to make appropriate modifications to the standard or policy; and
“(4) report annually to the Congress on—“(A) deficiencies in the standards and policies of Federal agencies for compromising, writing-down, forgiving, or discharging indebtedness; and
“(B) progress made in improving those standards and policies.”
